---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SectionHeading from "../components/ui/SectionHeading.astro";
import Button from "../components/ui/Button.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Elizabeth Olivier | La Sprezzatura Interior Design"
  description="Meet Elizabeth Olivier, founder and principal designer of La Sprezzatura. Based on Long Island's North Shore, Elizabeth creates spaces that feel as beautiful as they do livable."
>
  <!-- Hero: Editorial layout with photo and name -->
  <section
    class="pt-16 md:pt-20 pb-0 px-6 max-w-[1200px] mx-auto"
    data-animate="fade-up"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-0 md:gap-16 items-end">
      <!-- Elizabeth portrait -->
      <div class="order-1 md:order-none">
        <div
          class="relative w-full aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden"
          aria-label="Photo of Elizabeth Olivier, founder of La Sprezzatura"
        >
          <img
            src="https://cdn.sanity.io/images/e9tpu2os/production/dac5e9586287d906adbc2bb2b8f52a4c17eae00c-534x732.jpg?w=800&h=1067&fit=crop&auto=format"
            alt="Elizabeth Olivier, founder and principal designer of La Sprezzatura"
            class="w-full h-full object-cover object-top"
            loading="eager"
            width="534"
            height="732"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Name and title -->
      <div class="pb-0 md:pb-12 pt-8 md:pt-0">
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta mb-4 font-body"
        >
          Principal Designer
        </p>
        <h1
          class="font-heading text-5xl md:text-7xl font-light text-charcoal leading-none mb-4"
        >
          Elizabeth<br />Olivier
        </h1>
        <p class="font-body text-stone-dark tracking-wide text-sm uppercase">
          Founder & Principal Designer
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 w-16 h-px bg-terracotta"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Story Section -->
  <section
    class="py-16 md:py-24 px-6"
    data-animate="fade-up"
  >
    <div
      class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto md:ml-auto md:mr-0 md:pr-8 lg:pr-24 xl:pr-0 xl:max-w-[900px] xl:mx-auto"
    >
      <p
        class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-charcoal italic leading-relaxed mb-8"
      >
        "Interior design is more than choosing beautiful things — it's about
        creating spaces that feel like an exhale."
      </p>
      <div
        class="font-body text-charcoal leading-[1.9] space-y-6 text-base md:text-lg"
      >
        <p>
          Spaces where you can set down the day and truly be home. That belief
          is at the heart of everything I do at La Sprezzatura.
        </p>
        <p>
          The name comes from an Italian concept I've always loved: <em>sprezzatura</em> — the
          art of making something difficult look effortless. Behind every seemingly simple design
          choice are hundreds of considered decisions: the right depth of a sofa, the layering
          of textiles, the way light falls across a room at four in the afternoon. I want my
          clients to walk into a finished room and feel it was always meant to be this way — even
          though nothing about it was accidental.
        </p>
        <p>
          I came to interior design through an unusual path. I spent years in the luxury rug and
          carpet industry, developing an almost obsessive knowledge of fibers, weaves, and
          artisan production — the kind of knowledge that lets me source a room-defining rug that
          will look as beautiful in twenty years as it does today. That foundation in materials
          and craftsmanship shapes how I approach every project: start with what you can touch,
          and build the room from the ground up.
        </p>
        <p>
          Design is personal, so I pay attention. When a client hesitates over a fabric swatch,
          I notice. When someone's eyes light up at a particular blue, I remember — and it shows
          up in the welcome package I send them, wrapped with ribbon and a handwritten note. I
          believe the best design comes from paying attention to the things people don't say out loud.
        </p>
        <p>
          Based in Northport on Long Island's North Shore, I bring a blend of coastal ease and
          metropolitan sophistication to every project. I speak English, Spanish, and Italian
          fluently — and enough Portuguese to get by — which reflects the multicultural sensibility
          I bring to my work. Whether it's a full home renovation or refreshing a single room, I
          approach each space as a conversation: your life, your history, your style, refined
          through a designer's eye.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Design Philosophy -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 px-6 bg-cream-dark" data-animate="fade-up">
    <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
      <SectionHeading tagline="What I believe">
        Design Philosophy
      </SectionHeading>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 md:gap-12">
        {
          [
            {
              principle: "Sentimental design",
              description:
                "Your home already has a story. I work with what you love — an heirloom chair, a piece of art, a rug from your travels — and build around it. The best rooms don't erase the past; they honor it.",
            },
            {
              principle: "Three choices, not thirty",
              description:
                "Too many options paralyze. I listen first, then present a curated few that I believe in completely. When I show you something, it's because I've already done the editing for you.",
            },
            {
              principle: "The details you can touch",
              description:
                "A room is defined by its materials. The spring of wool underfoot, the weight of a linen drape, the grain of a walnut tray — I choose pieces for how they feel in daily life, not just how they photograph.",
            },
            {
              principle: "Comfort is not negotiable",
              description:
                "Beautiful spaces must also be livable. A room you're afraid to use isn't well-designed — it's staged. I want you to kick off your shoes and sink into the sofa. That's success.",
            },
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="group">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
                <div
                  class="w-1 h-full min-h-[3rem] bg-terracotta flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                  aria-hidden="true"
                />
                <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl font-light text-charcoal leading-tight">
                  {item.principle}
                </h3>
              </div>
              <p class="font-body text-stone leading-relaxed pl-5">
                {item.description}
              </p>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Personal Touches -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6" data-animate="fade-up">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-stone mb-8 font-body">
        Background
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3
            class="font-heading text-lg font-light text-charcoal mb-3 leading-tight"
          >
            Rug & Textile Expertise
          </h3>
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-stone leading-relaxed">
            Years in the luxury carpet industry gave me deep knowledge of fibers,
            artisan weaving, and material sourcing — from hand-knotted Persian to
            custom-milled broadloom.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3
            class="font-heading text-lg font-light text-charcoal mb-3 leading-tight"
          >
            Northport, Long Island
          </h3>
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-stone leading-relaxed">
            Based on the North Shore and serving clients throughout Long Island
            and New York City. I volunteer with the Northport Historical Society
            and draw inspiration from the area's coastal character.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3
            class="font-heading text-lg font-light text-charcoal mb-3 leading-tight"
          >
            Three Languages
          </h3>
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-stone leading-relaxed">
            Fluent in English, Spanish, and Italian, with conversational
            Portuguese. I can recite — and explain the meaning of — a number
            of Italian arias, which is either a party trick or a design
            qualification, depending on who you ask.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3
            class="font-heading text-lg font-light text-charcoal mb-3 leading-tight"
          >
            Beyond the Studio
          </h3>
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-stone leading-relaxed">
            When I'm not designing, I'm usually cooking — gourmet meals for
            family and friends are my other creative outlet. The same instinct
            that layers textures in a room layers flavors on a plate.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Client Voices -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 px-6 bg-cream-dark" data-animate="fade-up">
    <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto">
      <SectionHeading tagline="In their words">
        Client Voices
      </SectionHeading>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        {
          [
            { quote: "We gave Elizabeth a living room we'd been avoiding for years and a vague idea of what we wanted. She came back with three options, each one better than the last. The room we ended up with feels like it's always been this way — which is exactly what she promised.", location: "Cold Spring Harbor" },
            { quote: "What impressed me most was how quickly Elizabeth understood our taste. We'd worked with two other designers who kept showing us things that felt wrong. Elizabeth nailed it on the first visit. She has an intuition for what people actually want to live with.", location: "Oyster Bay" },
            { quote: "Elizabeth is the most organized person I've ever worked with. Every timeline was met, every detail was tracked, and she made what should have been a stressful renovation feel completely manageable. I've already referred her to three friends.", location: "Manhasset" },
            { quote: "I was nervous about the budget, and Elizabeth never made me feel like my project was too small. She gave our guest bedroom the same care and attention I've seen other designers reserve for full-home renovations. The room is perfect.", location: "Lloyd Harbor" },
            { quote: "Elizabeth actually listened. She asked about how we use the space, what bothers us, what we love. By the time she presented her ideas, it felt like she'd been living in our house. That level of attention is rare.", location: "Huntington Bay" },
            { quote: "We've done three projects together now and I genuinely look forward to each one. Elizabeth has become the person I call before I buy anything for the house. She's not just our designer — she's our taste filter.", location: "Lattingtown" },
          ].map((t) => (
            <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-terracotta/40 pl-5 py-2">
              <p class="font-body text-sm text-charcoal leading-relaxed italic mb-2">
                "{t.quote}"
              </p>
              <cite class="font-body text-xs text-stone tracking-wide not-italic uppercase">
                — Client, {t.location}
              </cite>
            </blockquote>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section
    class="py-20 md:py-28 px-6 text-center"
    data-animate="fade-up"
  >
    <div class="max-w-[600px] mx-auto">
      <h2
        class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-light text-charcoal mb-6 leading-tight"
      >
        Let's create something beautiful together.
      </h2>
      <p class="font-body text-stone text-lg leading-relaxed mb-10">
        Every project begins with a conversation. Tell me about your space, and
        we'll figure out the rest together.
      </p>
      <Button href="/contact" size="lg">Get in Touch</Button>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
